span style=-ms-grid-row:13>7.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:13><p data-aid=139949243 id=note7_p1>Ironically, Cain’s slaying of Abel, an act ultimately directed by Satan, may have been linked to Cain’s earlier anger over his sacrificial offering being rejected by the Lord while Abel’s was accepted.</p><p data-aid=139949258 id=note7_p2>“God … prepared a sacrifice in the gift of His own Son, who should … open a door through which man might enter into the Lord’s presence. …</p><p data-aid=139949265 id=note7_p3>“By faith in this atonement or plan of redemption, Abel offered to God a sacrifice that was accepted, which was the firstlings of the flock. Cain offered of the fruit of the ground, and was not accepted. … [His sacrifice was to have included] the shedding of blood” (<cite>Teachings of Presidents of the Church: Joseph Smith</cite> [2007], <a class="" href=#note7>48</a>; see also <a class="" href=#note7>107–8</a>).</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:15>8.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:15><p data-aid=139949272 id=note8_p1><a class="" href=#note8>3 Nephi 9:19–20, 22</a>.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:17>9.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:17><p data-aid=139949281 id=note9_p1><a class="" href=#note9>Doctrine and Covenants 59:9</a>.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:19>10.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:19><p data-aid=139949290 id=note10_p1><a class="" href=#note10>Moroni 4:3</a>; <a class="" href=#note10>5:2</a>.</p></div><span style=-ms-grid-row:21>11.</span><div style=-ms-grid-row:21><p data-aid=139949297 id=note11_p1>“More Holiness Give Me,” <em>Hymns,</em> no. 131.</p></div></section></div></div></aside></div></main><div><div><script type=text/javascript> var channel = 'www.lds.org'; var pageName = 'www.lds.org:""'; var locale = '"eng"'; var LDS = LDS || { }; LDS.track = LDS.track || { }; LDS.track.pageName = pageName; LDS.track.channel = channel; LDS.track.prop35 = locale; if (typeof(searchType) !== 'undefined' && typeof(searchResults) !== 'undefined') {    LDS.tra